alias^#^
SUBTOPIC-player^#^
                    -=[ Help ]=-

       Command: alias
         Usage: alias <alias> <command>

   Description: The alias command allows you to substitute an
		alias for a command.  You are allowed to have 30 aliases.

		Some commands can not be used as an alias - things like
		say, for example. Other commands that creators use 
		are the same. This is because of the way that the functions
		are organised (i.e. are static). Static commands are designed
		so no one can 'command' you to do them, not even when it
		is yourself commanding them through an alias.

       Example: alias 1 buy beer

Related topics: do.
 
