alignment^#^
SUBTOPIC-player^#^
SYNOPSIS: Alignment and Titles


DESCRIPTION:
	Alignment is a measure of how good or how
	evil you are. The alignments, from most
	good to most evil are as follows.

		Lawful Good
		Lawful Neutral
		Neutral Good
		True Neutral
		Chaotic Neutral
		Neutral Evil
		Chaotic Evil

	While they do not exactly fit into the scheme of AD&D,
	the titles are used as a rough guide, and are not exactly
	comparable to that system.

	Basically, alignment works like this; the more 'good'
	a player, then the more 'evil' a monster he needs to
	kill in order to remain his current alignment.

	If he kills something not so evil, then his alignment
	will slide back toward neutral.

	Alignment is used in the game for the following things:
	* Affiliations, like the Robes of Alignment for Magic,
		and clerical orders.
	* Intelligent weapons.
	* Death (and the afterlife).

