affiliation^#^
SUBTOPIC-player^#^
		-=[ Affiliations ]=-

SYNOPSIS
	Affiliations are 'guild-like' player ascociations

DESCRIPTION
	An affiliation is, simply, a player run organisation. It is based
	around themes, classes, sub-classes, and many more things!

	Affiliations don't really give you any powers, or abilities, but
	function as social units you can join and belong to. Sometimes,
	when they are formed by high level players, you can gain some
	room, or special meeting place from it.

	Currently there are the following affiliations:

	The Robes of Alignment
	~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
	The Robes of Alignment are mages who understand the Unified Laws
	of Magic in all the realms. 

	They are organised into the white (good), grey (neutral), and
	black (evil) alignments, and gain extra magic power through
	their casting of spells which are complimentaty with their
	alignment energies.

	See the 'Law of Magic', or the Isle of Sorcery for more details.



	The Orders of Priesthood
	~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
	Mortals and beings of power serve the dieties of the realms of Magia.
	Currently there are two affiliations, or 'orders of priesthood' for
	players to join.

	Clerics of the All-God
	Priests of Antaaries


	See also: 'help gods' for a list of gods




ABILITIES
	All players can check the members and leaders of an affiliation
	by use of the following commands:
	
	leaders
	members

	Those who are leaders are able to admit new members:

	admit <name> as <member|leader>

	The same command is used when new leaders to an affiliation
	are needed. Since players run the affiliation they are responsible
	or looking after the politics of the society.

